20:
BLISTERIN' BARNACLES! What's the big
idea?!
24:
That hurt like a cutlass to the booty,
I'll say!
27: The heck did I do to deserve this?!
31: Well... You seem to be in one piece.
35:
Wait, where am I? And who are you
guys?
39:
Welcome to Starview Village. I am its
Keeper, Stella.
46:
Now this here's some good eatin'!
You're an absolute genius in the
galley!
49:
Appreciate the compliment. Makes
the hard work I put into cooking
worth it!
51:
I've never had anything even
remotely this good on the pirate
ship! It's usually just moldy old
bread...
55: So you're a pirate after all.
59:
The name's Hayz! I'm with the
Crimson Blades!
64:
Crimson Blades? You work for
Marina then?
69:
Sink me sideways! You know
Marina?!
73: Actually, we're also with the Crim—
79:
Marina's a total boss, ain't she? She's
tough, beautiful, and well-rounded
in all the right places—if y'know what
I mean! I'm stickin' with her till the
day I die!
84:
I don't believe I've ever seen you
aboard Marina's ship.
90:
About that, you gotta hear me out!
'Cuz I've got one heck of a tearjerker
for ya!
98:
I went off lookin' for a present for
Marina—something to put a huge
smile on her face!
100:
And that's when the Gaean Navy
caught me!
103:
I eventually found my way back, but
the ship wasn't around anymore!
108:
In other words, you got left behind.
Am I right?
114:
Like, what was I supposed to do?! I
had no idea where Marina and the
rest of the Crimson Blades were!
116:
Anyhoo, I knew I had to get back to
her. So I plunged into the sea!
123:
And that's when I realized... that I
don't actually know how to swim.
127:
Hold on—you're a pirate, but you
can't swim?
130: I could feel my body fallin'.
134:
But yo-ho-ho, as fate would have it,
mermaids came to my rescue!
137:
Strange thing is though, they then
tossed me onto some weird gizmo.
140:
And before I knew it, I ended up here
with you landlubbers!
144:
This guy's obviously not the sharpest
cutlass on the ship.
147:
Okay, we understand your plight,
but...
151:
So what are your plans now? We
can help you get back to the sea if—
156:
Ain't it obvious?! I'm comin' with you
guys!
158:
Any friend of Marina is a friend of
mine! We were destined to come
together!
161:
I happen to be a pretty good shot,
you know! Watch this!
171:
Hm, not bad. Your accuracy is
impressive.
176:
You can say that again! I bet you
can't wait to bring me along!
178:
These twin pistols are my pride and
joy! Marina gave 'em to me as
congrats for pullin' off my first big
job!
183:
Are you sure about this? Shouldn't
you be with the Crimson Blades
inste—
